  fiber: 3 g
  sodium: 1240 mg
servings: 2
author: HelloFresh
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/balsamic-chicken-mozzarella-sandwiches-6553c9dd86d0f72f966fe450
time required: 15 minutes
cuisine: Southern Europe
course: main course
---

Wash and dry produce.

Slice @fresh mozzarella{4%ounce} into rounds.

Slice @tomato{1} into rounds; season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Pat @chicken cutlets{10%ounce} dry; slice crosswise. Place in a large #bowl{}
and season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Add half the @creamy balsamic dressing{1.5%ounce}
and turn to coat.

Drizzle @cooking oil{1%teaspoon} in a hot large pan. Add chicken; cook until
browned and cooked through, ~{5-7%minutes} per side.

In the last minute of cooking, carefully top chicken with sliced mozzarella;
cover pan until cheese melts.

> While chicken cooks, move on to the next step!

In a second large bowl, toss @arugula{4%ounce} with half the @balsamic glaze{5%teaspoon},
a large drizzle of @olive oil{2%teaspoon}, @salt{}, and @pepper{}.

Halve and toast @ciabatta roll{2%unit}.

Spread cut sides of ciabatta halves with as much @mayonnaise{2%tablespoon}
as you like. Place chicken on bottom ciabatta halves; top with @tomato{1} and
drizzle with as much remaining balsamic glaze as you like. Close sandwiches.

Gently crush @croutons{2%unit} in #bag{}.

Top salad with croutons and @walnuts{1%ounce}; serve alongside sandwiches.

> Chicken is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 165°.